(151, 'alphaville', 63, 9, 'I wish I could remember the name of the lead actor.. smokes a great cigarette... plays the part of Lemmie Caution.  The basic plot is that a planet in a far off galaxy has been taken over by computers and the rule of logic. The bible in the hotel draw is actually the dictionary, and each day a new one is bought with fewer words in.  More economical, miss out words that upset the workings, like ''love'' or ''family''.  );\r\ninsert into videos values (Lemmie Caution sorts them out.  Inter-stellar space in this instance is the ring road in and around Paris.  It''s very pop-art meets film noir, in that it''s in black and white with lots of neon and shadows, reported speech over in the third person.  I like this film.'),
